17 day of that month."
18 SECTION 2.
19 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 47-25-80, relating to requirements
20 to receiving benefits, as follows:
21 "47-25-80.
22 (a) In order for a member to be eligible to receive retirement benefits under this chapter,
23 he or she must have:
24 (1) Served as a regularly qualified and commissioned chief magistrate or as the
25 secretary-treasurer for at least eight years;
26 (2) Fully complied with this chapter;
27 (3) Terminated his or her official capacity as a chief magistrate or as the
28 secretary-treasurer;
29 (4) Attained the age of 60 55 years;
30 (5) Filed with the board his or her application for such retirement, on a form to be
31 furnished by the board, within a period of 90 days, or as soon thereafter as possible, after
32 reaching the age of 60 55 years or after termination of his or her official capacity as a
33 chief magistrate or as the secretary-treasurer, whichever may occur last in point of time;
34 and
35 (6) Had his or her application for retirement approved by the board.
36 (b) If a member retires prior to the age of 60, his or her benefit, as calculated pursuant to
37 Code Section 47-25-81, shall be reduced by one-twelfth of 3 percent for each month by
38 which his or her age at the time of retirement is below 60 years."
